z = x + iy
\dfrac{1}{z} = \dfrac{1}{ x + iy}. \tag{1}
1 = \dfrac{x - iy}{x - iy}: \tag{2}
\dfrac{1}{z} = \dfrac{(x - iy) \times 1}{(x - iy)(x + iy)} = \dfrac{x - iy}{x^2 + y^2}, \tag{3}
(x - iy)(x + iy) = x^2 + y^2
